inn1.comm: bounce, back of a length, inward seam too, but it came off slowly, already, and is tucked to the leg side off the toes
pitched up, around the off stump, slowish off the pitch once again, Gambhir gets front foot out and pats it away
left alone outside the off stump now as it bounces across the left-hander
outside edge as he is slightly squared up with a length ball around off, away to third man
away movement after pitching on a good length, but too far outside off, and left alone
Finn shouts for lbw, but that length ball took a huge inside edge first before travelling sideways to hit pad as Rahane pushed half-forward
there is some carry here from short of a good length, Gambhir on his toes to bring it down
similar length, but he gets some width to steer it towards point, who goes flying to his right to deny them the run
in swing now, down the leg side, and the crowd goes nuts as it bounces in front of the keeper and runs to the boundary
better line, much better, defended down the pitch
Dernbach on the leg stump again, carrying on from Rajkot, Gambhir helping it to fine leg
straightening from a good length around off, he waits and runs it to third man

loud, bent-knee, imploring appeal for lbw from Dernbach, but the inswinging delivery was going down the leg side, looks much closer on impact than real time on replay, which also show it pitching outside leg
right on middle stump, England sticking to largely back of a length stuff, defended
and then he bowls a full toss on the pads, but Gambhir works it straight to fine leg
pitched up, around off, he takes a step out and eases it to mid off
angled in, middle and leg, Rahane works it away nicely, but square leg is in the way
well bowled, straightens and lifts from short of a length, Rahane handles it well too, steering it past slip to third man

looks straight, looks a fine appeal this, Gambhir caught on the pad stretching far forward on the defence, good length ball, did it pitch outside leg, umpire Kulkarni unmoved? replays awaited, seems to be a thin inside edge, also marginal call whether it pitched in line with leg
punched to cover from the crease
dropped, thick chunk of an edge is put down by a diving keeper in front of first slip, but England's immediate cause of dismay is that umpire Davis calls it a wide, has to be the decibel level
steered to point off the back foot
goes after a widish length ball, drives it over backward point

this might be called the Gambhir guided-dab in years to come, wonder how he ends up playing the shot every time as if on auto pilot, moving away from good length, and he hangs out an angled bat at it, ball squeezes into the gap between first slip and a wider slip

outstanding stuff from Dernbach, the previous one zipped away, this one comes in slightly after pitching on a good length on off, Gambhir driving at the original angle, enough of a gap between bat and pad for the stumps to take a blow
there is some seam serious movement going on out there, this one comes screaming in from way outside off as Rahane leaves it seeing the original line, wasn't too far from off in the end
and now this one moves away from the right hander, does not get up too much, too many variables, Rahane beaten totally on the cut

bowled 'em, inswing accompanied with seam this time, Rahane has been tentative to get forward, and it has caused his downfall, goes across a bit in the crease to a good length delivery outside off, and defends far away from the body, ball swings in late, and disturbs another set of stumps through the wide-open gate
Yuvraj, hanging the bat outside off Gambhir fashion, but withdraws it late as this one angles across
worked to square leg
left alone outside off
slight, slight away shape, the kind that takes outside edges, Yuvraj fortunate enough to be beaten as he pushes around off
worked through square leg
kicks outside off, Kohli shoulders arms
lovely once more, angled in a bit, holding its line, not that far from off stump, left alone again
the attempted cuts have looked quite dangerous, for the batsmen, Kohli almost playing on as he goes for the stroke, gets a boundary fine down the leg side
Kohli moving across steadily now, covering the line of off, allowing a straightening delivery to go past outside off, that is a start, as far as survival goes
and then there's the lack of bounce as well, good length delivery dying in front of the keeper as it is angled across widish outside off
played out towards midwicket
banged in short, Yuvraj wanting to pull, but early into the shot, and is hit on the body, the ball scoots behind point, variable bounce, slow bounce, seam, swing, bat-first pitch?
right on middle stump, pitched-up, pushed to mid on
short of a length, comes slowly off the pitch, Kohli on his toes to block
good length, uses the angle to work it away, but straight to square leg
extravagant seam movement across the left-hander, like a fast offbreak
now one that holds its line on leg stump, short of a length, worked behind square
worked away wide of midwicket
Yuvraj giving the crowd reason to roar, wide away moving back of a length ball, punched on the toes crisply through covers
on middle, tucked off the pads now, in front of square leg, stopped inches before the rope
opens the face to a widish length ball and runs it to square third man, the crowd has almost brought the roof down, already
length ball around off and middle, tucked through midwicket calmly
thick inside edge as he defends one going across on a good length, Kohli hurries across, Yuvraj gets going ultimately too
almost guided it to the keeper, Kohli trying to find the single to third man, ball just misses the outside edge
leg side, fullish, flicked to fine leg
not quite off the middle of the bat, but a swivelling Yuvraj will get four past square leg for his pull
beaten, Finn gets the line right off the last ball of the over, leaving Yuvraj from a good length around off
starts too far wide outside off for the away movement to bother Kohli
another attempted cut, another thick inside edge, and closer to hitting the stumps this time than Kohli's previous attempt, ball wasn't wide enough for the shot
Woakes settling in already, angled in, good length, around off, and leaving Kohli, whose attempt to fiddle with it does not produce an edge
pitched up, front foot goes out, and he drives it solidly to the bowler
handles the lift from short of a length and steers it to third man
a back-foot punch but not timed well enough to beat the bowler
full, on the pads, stylish flick straight to Cook at short midwicket, almost carried, almost
stays low from a good length, middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
thick outside edge past the slip, short third man goes sprawling across the turf to keep them to one
was eyeing the slog sweep initially, but then saw it fuller outside off, and drove it to covers
almost popped it to extra cover, Kohli driving in the air, it hung limply in space for some time, but fielder could not get to it
defended off the front foot
back of a length, on leg stump, Yuvraj played this shot well in Rajkot too, one leg in the air as he swings it wristily behind square leg
similar delivery, pulled through square leg this time
pitch easing out now, pitched up delivery angling in to the batsman, tucked square to leg
beaten, Yuvraj not comfortable with that line leaving him outside off stump from a good length, tries to steer it, cannot connect
leg side again with the line and an easy single to square leg
stays balanced and defends a pitched up delivery around off stump
turning in to the pads from over the wicket, nudged to short fine
Yuvraj lunges down for the sweep, misses the line as it spins in, hit on the pad but that was headed comfortably down leg
misses again, charges out now, has a swing but hit on the body
better from Yuvraj, moves forward in solid defence
flat, wide, straight and put away off the back foot through point
played out down the pitch
flicked with the incoming angle to fine leg
Yuvraj playing some lovely strokes now, slowness of the pitch allows him to stay on the crease to a good length ball and punch it down the ground, too much in the end for the chasing mid off

and then he is beaten immediately outside off stump, as this one jags away from a good length, England put in half an appeal, umpire Davis shakes his head, was that an edge? The on-air commentator Laxman Sivaramakrishnan thinks it was, a very faint one, impossible to hear that with this crowd, if it was one
left alone with the angle outside off now
walks down the pitch now, runs the length ball towards point
front foot out towards the line of one leaving him, and lifts the bat out of the line
pushed off the front foot towards short third
angled in, and spins in further down leg as Yuvraj misses the nudge
tossed up, full, squeezed out to extra cover
angled in slower, nudged to square leg
worked behind square leg
goes back in the crease to a length ball hurrying in, brings bat down in time and takes a run to square leg
slog swept powerfully, but deep square leg will get to it
tossed up from round the stumps, defended off the front foot

given leg-before this time, Yuvraj not looking particularly happy, he has a few words to say as he walks back, the source of his dismay is that he gloved the attempted sweep onto the pad, although he was struck in front of the stumps
thick outside edge as he stretches forward to one straightening outside off, pulled back inside the third man rope
bowling a lovely line on off stump, flighted full, blocked
whoa, Raina moving to the leg side a bit, the flighted ball stays in the air long enough for him to do a rethink, and just stab it away even as it hurries for the stumps
much quicker now on the stumps, defended off the front foot
played out to point off the front foot
the wristy whip-drive making an appearance after some time, straight to wide long off
spins in from outside off stump, Raina misses as he looks to work it to leg
Raina succeeds in nudging with the spin now, but square leg is there
bowls it full and wide of off now, pushed to extra cover
that kicked in from outside off, fortunately for Raina he wasn't into a stroke by then, fends it to the leg side from the crease
opens the face and runs it to the off side
quicker now, headed for off, bat coming down in time
worked to square leg
spins in sharply, and bounces off pad, keeper takes it on the leg side
good length, whipped to deep midwicket
Raina with the slog-sweep and the crowd comes alive, it was angled in towards the pads, but a lunging Raina was able to adjust and slam it over deep midwicket
driven to sweeper cover
played out to short midwicket
low full toss eased to long on
goes half-forward to smother a quicker one angled in
appeal for lbw as this one carries in with the arm, but there was some bat too as Kohli pushed at it
goes deep and opens up to whip it through midwicket
flatter one steered to backward point
stays back as one angles in to middle and leg, punched to the off side
fine cut, this time Kohli times the shot, moving back quickly, but sweeper does not have to move much to cut it off, probably key could be to look to play it in front of square on this pitch
defended tightly from the crease
just survived, just, wanted to pull a length ball that went straight on, and almost took off the bails, about half an inch over them in the end
wants to bash it out of sight now, mistimed to the bowler
better, drives a full one to long off
leading edge dies down the pitch as he looks to work to leg from off
manages to nudge it with the spin, wide of short fine
looked set to jump out initially, then stayed in the crease, ball stayed a bit low too in the end, stabbed away to the off
Raina steps out, is nowhere to the pitch, and pads it away in the air to the off side
straight to square leg after being nudged with the spin
moves forward to the pitch and works it past a diving midwicket to long on
quite some turn, jabbed away towards point
on the pad, to square leg for a single
went back and punched it between the sweeper and long off, adjusted as the ball stayed low
fine leg not really that fine and Raina has an easy single as he nudges one fine
through midwicket for a single
defended off the front foot
full delivery, he mistimes the push, midwicket cuts it off
dabbed very late to third man
a charge out and an emphatic lofted shot with the turn over extra cover, timed well enough to go all the way
punched to cover-point from the crease, another one staying a bit low
pushed wide of extra cover
lunging forward to get to the pitch and working it in front of square leg
not wide enough for the cut, but Raina watching it closely and opening the face to find the gap between backward point and short third man
pushed to the sweeper for one
steps down the track, the length is shortened, pushed down to long on
staying on the crease to a pitched up delivery, opens the face to push it the off
worked to leg for a single
not getting up much, Raina was eyeing the pull initially, but the pushes it back to the bowler
nudged with the spin straight to short fine leg
sharp, sharp turn into Raina, who is surprised as it hits the bat high and has no clue where it's gone, it falls close to him
wrists it to deep midwicket after a big forward stride
tossed up, pushed away off the front foot
defended off the front foot back to the bowler
squared him up, straightens on off stump, outside edge towards third man
pushed to extra cover
opens up and works with the spin to deep midwicket
full and angled in, played to mid on

Kohli has holed out, he's thrown away a hard-earned start, stepping out and slicing a full delivery to the man at sweeper cover, he slams the bat into the ground and makes a disappointed-with-himself exit
back of a length, defended
shortish, played out to point
steered from close to the body to third man
away with a single to the sweeper off a widish delivery
front foot across to the line outside off and works it to midwicket
goes across with the front foot again and nudges in the air to square leg
turned softly to square leg
pushes at a spinning delivery, gets it to cover
turn away from off stump, staying a tad low again, pushed to point
tries to cut another one that does not get up much, away to point again
walks across and down the pitch, pushes a length ball to the bowler and hurries back
kicking from short of a length, he slams it off the back foot past extra cover
fine drive from Dhoni, free-flowing followthrough off front foot, extra cover dives and saves runs
into the pads and helped wide of fine leg

caught behind appeal not given, England are absolutely convinced, umpire Kulkarni is not, bowler is running down the pitch in celebration even as he appeals, held its line just enough as Dhoni pushed at it, can't spot a deviation from the replays, sound suggests there was a thin edge, there was a sound definitely as ball passed bat, England denied, can't blame the umpires for failing to pick up faint snicks in so much noise
defended off the front foot
the Raina slog-sweep makes an appearance, picks it from off stump, and sends the ball deep into the crowd over deep midwicket
pushed to sweeper cover
spins in, stays low, and is worked to deep midwicket
lured out by all the flight, thick inside edge sends the ball to midwicket as he tries to drive through off
another thick inside edge, to the bowler as he eyes off again
pushes a back of a length ball to covers
smacks a furious cut, but sweeper cover scrambles to his left to cut it off
goes across and pushes a length ball to the bowler
opens the face and runs the ball to third man
steps across and down the pitch and flails a length ball in the air, fortunately it is wide of point
back of a length on the pads, tucked to deep square
full and squeezed past the bowler to long off
lunges towards the pitch, holding the bat at an angle all the time, wanting the single to the leg side, one of the most aware ODI batsmen ever
defended from the crease
turned to midwicket
manages to nudge with the spin to midwicket for one
pushed off the front foot to leg for a single
worked behind square leg off the pad
angled in full, Dhoni manages some wood on it and scampers down as it rolls close to the pitch
gets bat around front pad but cannot get the ball past short fine
whipped with the spin down to long on
straightens sharply on leg, and Dhoni adjusts to defend it
stretches forward and pushes it past the non-striker to long on
full on middle, Dhoni sends it softly to midwicket
bends the knee and brings bat around it to tuck it to short fine
full again, and again Dhoni pats it to midwicket,
goes back and to the leg side, and forces a length ball to long on
stretching fully forward in defence, ball scurries to leg and the single is on
shortish, Dhoni having all the time to set himself up for the big punch through off, but finding no timing in the end as it comes slowly into him, thick inside edge to leg
Raina gets a feather on one headed down the leg side, Cook races after it from short fine and hauls it back
full, pushed down to long on
staying low, Dhoni on the crease and whipping it to long on
digs out a fuller one , bowler cannot stop it with a dive, Morgan gets to it running across from short midwicket
full and angled in, worked softly to vacant midwicket, and they will take two
and Raina tries to slog the first ball over midwicket, thick inside edge down to short fine
fab touch from Raina, just a touch with an open-faced bat sends the ball racing past backward point, that is also 50 for Raina
opens the face again, this time the good length ball goes to third man
back of a length, pushed out to sweeper cover
slower one cutting across from back of a length, he hops across and nudges it behind square
Dhoni trying to cut one too close to the body, and getting beaten
Dernbach gets away with a short and wide one, Raina bashing it to Morgan at backward point
good length, tucked off the pads wide of midwicket
Dhoni slammed Dernbach down long off's throat in Rajkot, this time he's taken one on the full as he walks across and dismisses it to the straight boundary
goes across and lets a length ball go to the keeper outside off
and again, he lets a pitched up widish delivery go past him outside off
slower from Dernbach, Dhoni moving across again but only manages to push it wide of extra cover, who fields and makes Dhoni send a charging Raina back
angled wide across the left-hander, Dhoni asking umpire Davis why it wasn't called one, marginal call
slow bouncer now closer to off, Raina misses with the pull
has a flail at one leaving him outside off, misses once more
Raina gets width and delays his stroke to try and find the deep backward point rope, but third man denies him
walking across and tucking a back of a length ball behind square leg, it is in the gap and almost rolls into the rope before a slide from the running deep square leg
slower one, under 120 kph, Raina can't do anything about it, he tries to run it to third man, misses
tries a sweep from way outside off, misses
lunges forward, and allows yet another wide one to go away, probably Dhoni thought it was one, but it swung in slightly, and was just about okay in the end
now he charges out and has a wild swing which does not connect with anything
India making a mess of the Powerplay, now Dhoni mishits a full toss to mid on
slower one straightening wide outside off, Dhoni can only force it to mid on
full and down to third man
Raina misses out, length ball down the pads, and flicked into the hands of short fine leg

nothing powerful about India's batting Powerplay, Raina slogs at a length offcutter from Finn, and inside edging it onto his stumps, Finn has done a pretty good job with the slower one today, Raina gives himself a disappointed send-off, banging the bat on his helmet
he goes across and nudges a length ball off middle and leg through square
moves outside the line and works it to deep square leg, hopping as he does so
short, wide, cut straight to backward point
back of a length, pushed down the pitch to mid off
whips a length ball in front of square leg for two
can't work this one past the bowler, who threatens to throw it back, has a glance at the non-striker and walks back with a smile
a couple wide of fine leg now with a tuck off the pad
good length, right on off, defended solidly
works a short of a length ball away, but straight to midwicket
finds midwicket once more, but makes the man run a bit to his right, and the single is on
straightening on off stump, tight line right away, patted towards point
worked to square leg
length ball to Dhoni, who forces it to midwicket and gets across in no time
full, and a nudge past square leg brings another single
Dhoni picks the gap this time, whips with the spin behind square leg, past short fine
looking to charge out, stays back to a flat length ball and keeps strike with a single to covers
Dhoni picks the first ball from Woakes from outside off and slams it over deep midwicket
and then he moves towards the line and allows a widish one to go, he's done that a lot today
Dhoni down the pitch, squeezes a low full toss towards the bowler, who goes down quickly to field, and recovers immediately to be prepared to throw it back, sending Dhoni into the crease
away to extra cover for one
slow offcutter, mid off is up, Jadeja has a go, beats the infield and the ball bounces once before going over the rope
went full now on the stumps, Jadeja looking to go leg side, ends up going off instead with a leading edge
Jadeja works a length ball straight to midwicket
can't get it away, Tredwell extremely accurate, Jadeja pushes off the front foot and sets off, extra cover is around to send him back
third dot ball in a row in the 44th over as Jadeja cannot pinch a single on the off side, point cuts him off now
fourth one on the run, without one, Jadeja forces it to the leg side now, to midwicket
and an excellent front foot defence down the pitch now
a single, just a single off the over, Jadeja pulls in the gap between long on and deep midwicket, but he's neither timed nor powered it
Jadeja finding it difficult to get off strike now, forces a full one back to the bowler, Dhoni walks up to have a word
wonder what Dhoni told him, as next ball Jadeja sends one soaring into the stands way over long on, full around off, and he slams it out of sight
hits a full one back to the bowler again now
a high full toss, bowled wide too, and Jadeja puts it away through backward point
alternating between hitting a four and finding the bowler, the latter now
and next ball, he is back to hitting another four, going at more than a run a ball, full delivery, and Jadeja whips it through midwicket into the gap
slow, very slow at 112 kph, it is from the back of the hand, and moves away like a legbreak outside off
Dhoni gets another full and wide one, this time he is not leaving it, but is also not going any further than point
smacks a slow and pitched-up delivery to long on
back of the hand slower one, Dhoni steps out, waits for it, and hammers it over long off
full, wide, Dhoni immediately on the knee with a bee-sting of a drive, sweeper cover somehow manages to save the boundary
Jadeja playing a crucial innings here, pitched up, in the left-hander's slot around off, and he has picked it over midwicket
hit on the thigh pad as he fails to work a back of a length ball to leg
jumps out, but makes no contact as he swings hard
slow, good length, Dhoni opens up to slap it powerfully, straight to the sweeper though
Jadeja taking a step to leg to make room, but Finn negating that with a tight one on the stumps, inside edged to off for a single
Dhoni, easily one of the greatest ODI batsmen ever, gets to yet another fighting fifty with a pile-driver of a straight helicopter shot along the ground
and again, through midwicket this time, full into Dhoni, and he dismisses it with that unique deep-in-the-crease batswing of his
low full toss, but Jadeja mistimes a heave out to wide long on
full, around the blockhole wide outside off, Dhoni squeezes it out for one
very full again, but Jadeja mistimes again, gets two for the effort through midwicket
Jadeja succeeds third time, serious thwack of a connection as the ball flies in the gap between deep midwicket and long on, that's his region
angled across, slapped away to the sweeper
full, not that bad an over in the end, Dhoni tries to helicopter another boundary down the ground, but this time he will only find long on
wide, Dhoni is long past letting them go, he has cut it with everything he has, and he has a lot, the ball has zoomed over backward point
missed out, was eyeing deep midwicket as he swung, but missed the length ball angled in
helicopter on the off side for want of a better description, on the bounce to wide long off, who barely manages to stop it
Dhoni, you brutal, battering ram of a beauty, helicopters raining all around Kochi, Finn not missing the blockhole by much, enough for Dhoni to murder it over midwicket
Finn keeps the nerve to target the blockhole again, hits it, Dhoni's attempt at another helicopter ends at midwicket
slow, short, Jadeja upto it, drags a pull over square leg in he circle, the Kochi crowd may just end up with a collective bad throat with all that yelling
Dhoni has gone berserk with the helicopter stroke this afternoon, he;s walked to the off side, and swung a full delivery from close to the tramline over midwicket, incredible
on the outer side of the tramline with the full delivery as Dhoni charges out, and this one will be called a wide
Dhoni goes, finally, after one more fighting, counter-attacking, masterly ODI innings, taken at sweeper cover right at the edge of the rope
full and wide, Ashwin's underedge sends it to the keeper, batsmen scamper a single
Jadeja gets to a half-century with another dragging, heaving pull that takes the slow, short delivery wide of short fine leg
Ravindra Jadeja making a stirring case for the No 7 allrounder's position with a flowing pick-up off the pads over backward square leg
and another boundary, ballistic, cracking, finish for the Jamnagar boy, length delivery, Jadeja crashes it over deep midwicket as Kochi shouts itself hoarse

inn2.comm: angled wide across the left-hander, who thinks about going after it, but lets it be
moving away from a good length, guides it backward of point, who dives and keeps them to one
forces a good length ball back to the bowler
moves across, gets behind the line of a back of a length ball and defends
moving away sharply from some way outside off
short of a length, blocked out to cover
reaches out to a wide one and slaps it down to third man
starts with a length ball down leg
skids in from a good length, thick inside edge off pad to the leg side

gone, Shami pitching it up wide for the drive, and getting it to swing away appreciably, Bell chasing it, and only managing an edge to Dhoni, would have been called a wide had Bell not meddled with it
short of a length and is met by Pietersen on the walk, defended
he is making it swing sharply, at decent pace too, 137 kph good length, angled in, drawing KP into hanging his bat out as it swerves away
angled into the right-hander and dribbled behind square off pad
fine first ball to the left-hander from round the stumps, swinging in a tad, ending  on off, worked to midwicket
KP creating his own hitting space as always, walking across to turn a length ball from outside off to leg, midwicket in the way
and he succeeds, KP stays back, gets one on the pads and happily turns it to fine leg
thick outside edge to a length ball, rolls to point
not too much width but Cook still is able to squeeze it out to third man
opens the face to a good length ball and runs it tot third man
good length, punched from the crease, excellent timing from the captain, extra cover ends up escorting it to the rope
tries to lure KP into a drive outside off with a pitched up outswinger, KP has none of it
hit on the pad with one angled in, slips have a shout, but that was headed down leg
neat, Cook forward to an overpitched delivery and easing it through extra cover, Ishant Sharma won;t be stopping that
super, angled in from round the stumps and then holds its line sharply to beat Cook
too full, too much angle into the pads, and Cook is not missing out, he flicks it in front of square in the air
bounce from short of a length outside off, left alone
137 kph good length delivery outside off, holding its line, blocked
into the pads with the angle and worked behind square
again Cook quick on the cut, despite little with, there is a short cover-point
pushes it from close to the body to point
that came in a tad, also stayed very low, Cook went across and stabbed an inside edge onto pad
extra cover runs across and dives to keep Cook to one this time
from round the stumps, good length, left alone outside off
Cook gets the width and is eager to cut, Kohli gets down to his right quickly at backward point
holding its line, after being angled in, blocked
hit on the pads with a slippery 136.4 kph length ball, headed down leg though
good length right on off, pushed to mid on
moving away slightly, widish outside off, Cook beaten on the cut for once
well bowled, that straightened from a length outside off, just past the outside edge with keeper standing up
driven through the gap at cover, two men after it, Rahane reaches it and KP has two by that time
line gone wrong now for Bhuvneshwar, angled in from wide of the crease to the pad, and KP gets enough bat on it
pushes a length ball on off hard down the pitch, mid on gets across to it
mistimes a drive to mid on now
forced past the non-striker's stumps for a quick run
Shami has KP driving a pitched up delivery, there's the edge, but it is flying past second slip on the bounce
there's KP at his best, walking across, couple of steps out, and whipping a length ball from off to the deep square leg rope
beaten on the cut now as it moves in from a good length and also stays a bit low
pitched up at nearly 140 kph, pushed in front of extra cover, Yuvraj misses on the run, KP would have made it anyway
could have been close, length ball on the stumps, Cook gets bat down just in time to inside edge it to pad
misses the pull but the length ball is well down the leg side

somehow KP has hit a boundary to deep point while trying to whip it to the on side, the length ball scurries into the gap between cover and point, Jadeja barely pulls it back, Rahane slides to pick it up, but his foot's touched the rope
beaten on the cut with a good length ball angled across
drives a pitched up delivery but the off side infield is packed, extra cover fields
pushed off the front foot to wide mid off
pushed again, to wide mid off again

top effort from Raina creating a chance in the field and stopping a four, Cook thrashing a cut, but Raina quick to react to his left at short cover-point, another fielder aims at the non-striker's end but misses

run out chance missed now, Dhoni not pleased at all, Jadeja at midwicket failing to pick up the ball cleanly after a mix-up between the batsmen, Cook was very late to respond as KP charged down for the single
KP down the track right away, KP beaten with away movement from back of a length, but at the crease, it is a wide, and is called one
powerful response, length ball outside off and KP dismisses it with a meaty punch off the back foot past extra cover
lovely from KP again, he is stepping it up, full, angled in, KP's exaggerated across movement sets up the stroke as he whips it through midwicket
defended tightly off the front foot
walking, shuffling, flailing, whipping, KP gets a thick outside edge behind point now
played out to short midwicket
